<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
Trying a spectre troll possessor, I noticed that the pass wall ability did not disappear, even though I was inside a novice warrior corpse. Of course it is a nice thing (It's easy to imagine as a possessor with a corpse uncapable of opening doors should use this possibility), but it does not make sense to me.  <p>
Simon: seems you're possessing the ghost of that novice warrior! Congrats on the innovation! Too bad the -3 hit dice of spectres will partly affect your final HP... 
</p>
<p>
Carciofus: So I can do it without feeling guilty because of bug exploitation? 
</p>
<p>
Kalirion: Yeah, I don't think its a bug.  It's really similar to how a Lost Soul possessor can still pass through walls in the Halls of Mandos after possessing a body. 
</p>
